The paper discusses the challenges faced by database systems in catering to the growing demands of the information age, particularly in the context of natural language query interfaces. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the need for semantic cover over conventional query languages, which suggests that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
